Name: LEILA
Overall Comment: Awful hotel - with zero regards towards people with disabilities. Staff was kind and helpful, great people who tried helping us all along. Can't say enough about the girl at the lounge, the young fellows who helped us with wheelchair rides to navigate the hotel's 100% lack of accessibility.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: the hotel only had one type of accessible room - there was no way to provide an upgraded room with an accessible toilet/shower/etc. This is saying to customers who have disabilities that they do not deserve to be treated as people with no disability. The pool was another example of this. No access to a bathroom, or changing facilities. The changing room was 19 steps away from the pool deck, the pool has no accessibility -only wall steps that would not allow a person who is disabled to enter or exit the pool. The lounge elevator was cancelled (apparently for years now). Accessing the lounge meant going through a long way and jumping over an extra step. And another step to reach a bathroom (that was not accessible of course). The ramp access to the building did not have an automatic opener or even someone watching over - there was someone around the entrance, never watching the ramp access or helping. I guess you get an idea by now and I have not even yet described the   Buenos Aires hotel's concept of "accessible bathroom"

Overall Comment: I would not recommend this hotel. There are several other high end hotels in the area at similar price points that are much nicer. The room was very warm, and the thermostats did not appear to control anything. The food was not good, and made me sick one night. The service was not good either. It was impossible to reach the hotel before coming to stay, we tried multiple times to call based on number listed on bonvoy and what is listed online, and could not reach anyone or find an email address. When we finally got a hold of someone 2 days before travel, I only requested help with possible flowers in the room or a bottle of champagne waiting in room to help celebrate our anniversary. The response was I needed to reach out weeks ahead of time to set that up. Which seems difficult when you’ve made it impossible to get ahold of anyone. There were other issues, but honestly I don’t think you need an exhaustive list to understand why it was not a good stay. We checked out early and went to the Hyatt, which was by far a superior experience, for the same nightly rate. I have been on the fence about leaving Bonvoy to commit to Hyatt, but this will probably be the event that makes that decision easier for us.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: As stated earlier this was a very poor experience. It was so bad we checked out early to go to the local Hyatt. The Hyatt was so superior I wish we’d stayed there the whole time.

Name: JOSE
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
Buenos días soy Jose Maran de Uruguay el pasado fin de semana fui con mi esposa a Bs As  a una gala de opera en el Teatro Colon. Ese fin de semana la tarifa del hotel esbara por encima de lo que normalmente cobran, igualmente lo reserve   ya que estaba frente al Teatro. La habitación estaba correcta pero la vista era en muro lateral deteriorado es decir una vista deprimente (605) para el precio pagado. Pero lo que mas me molesto es que de tres ascensores solamente uno estaba en funcionamiento por lo cual tanto, subir como para bajar era una tortura.
El día de la partida estábamos frente al ascensor a las 11.55 y recién  llegamos a la recepción a las 12.15, los ascensores que subían venían siempre llenos y los de bajada igual, finalmente  pudimos tomar un ascensor, de subida, con 4 personas, fuimos hasta  el piso 17, parando en casi  todos los pisos tanto de subida como de bajada ya que en casi todos los pisos había huéspedes intentando tomar el ascensor.
Realmente la relación calidad precio fue pésima, seguramente una opción de 4 estrellas hubiese sido mas gratificante.

Name: ALEXANDRE
Overall Comment: Sempre dei preferência para o   em minhas hospedagens em Buenos Aires, porém dessa vez a experiência foi muito ruim. No último dia da minha estadia, percebi que entraram em meu quarto sem minha permissão, mesmo com o aviso de "não perturbe" na porta. Cheguei ao hotel depois de um dia exaustivo de trabalho, entrei em meu quarto e percebi que os itens do frigobar haviam sido removidos. Questionei à recepção se alguém havia entrado e eles não sabiam, pediram tempo para revisar as câmeras (precisavam acesso que só seria concedido no dia seguinte) e enviaram alguém da equipe para fazer algumas perguntas. Me orientaram a ficar tranquilo e descansar, pois eles estariam vigiando meu quarto, mas obviamente fiquei preocupado com a possibilidade de que alguém estranho tivesse acesso e pudesse entrar de surpresa. Fiquei com medo e ansioso, não consegui dormir e não pude descansar antes de sair para pegar meu voo. Ao fazer o check-out, o responsável pela segurança veio conversar comigo e dizer que haviam identificado que realmente um funcionário do hotel entrou em meu quarto para remover as bebidas do frigobar, de maneira equivocada (deveria fazer isso na outra torre, não na em que eu estava). De qualquer maneira, achei péssima a experiência, pois me senti exposto e inseguro. Com certeza voltarei a Buenos Aires (trabalho com frequência na região) e gosto muito do  , mas vou ter que pensar bem na hora de decidir onde ficar em minhas próximas visitas, infelizmente.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: O motivo já foi descrito em minha resposta à primeira pergunta desse questionário. Quero acreditar que tenha sido um ponto muito fora da curva, e que não se repita, dada a sua gravidade para a confiança que o   quer transmitir aos seus hóspedes e membros.

The ambiance was perfect, and we were enjoying our stay until a minor water leak occurred in our bathroom. Unfortunately, the hotel was fully booked that evening, and no vacant rooms were available for us to move to. 

However, the following morning, we were pleasantly surprised to receive an upgrade to a beautiful room on the 18th floor, which offered us breathtaking views of the heart of Buenos Aires. 
We were impressed with the level of attention and exceptional customer service provided by the hotel staff, including Celeste, Demian, Juan, and Noemi from the front desk/reception. All of them welcomed us warmly and made sure that we felt comfortable throughout our stay. Additionally, Luis in the breakfast room was always ready to serve us with a smile and went above and beyond to fulfill our requests. 

We would like to commend these individuals for their outstanding representation of the   family. We are confident that our friends and colleagues who plan to visit Buenos Aires will have an equally delightful experience at the Buenos Aires  , and we will certainly recommend it to them.

Name: LESLIE
Overall Comment: I stayed here two different times as I was going back and forth to Brazil.  The first was a one night stay on March 26.  And a two night stay beginning March 31.  I was upgraded to an Executive Suite without any requesting in advance or asking at the front desk at check in.  It was automatically tagged to my reservation!!  I so much appreciate this.  Then I also received a welcome gift in addition to benefits already requested!  Thanks for recognizing my Titanium status.  Also I want to point out the great service of Augustin at the front desk.  I had requested to store luggage on March 25 before my stay on March 26.  He handled it so perfectly and I felt well taken care of.  He also took some laundry for me to do.  Both the laundry and my luggage were awaiting in my room when I arrived.  When I checked out I asked why the laundry wasn't on my bill.  It was comped!!  All those gestures mean a lot to me!  And Augustin, but all your front desk staff as well, was very kind and helpful.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: I think your service and room quality is superior to many   brands I have stayed at.  It is comparable to a luxury brand.  I was truly satisfied.

Name: LUCAS
Overall Comment:
Hola! Quiero aclarar que el hotel está bien, pero no ayuda a tener una buena experiencia. Si bien lo que no me gustó son detalles, creo que son demasiados para un hotel de esta categoría. En otro tipo de hotel ni lo hubiera considerado, pero en esta ocasión fui buscando una buena experiencia.
En primer lugar, al momento de querer usar el sauna tuve el problema de que no podía encontrar una ducha libre entre las entradas al sauna (es decir, las duchas frías para cortar el calor). Si bien el vestuario es grande, y tiene una capacidad de lockers de 20, sólo hay 2 duchas. En los días es que estuve hubo muy poca gente, y el sauna siempre estuvo vacío. Incluso en la pileta no había demasiada gente. Por eso era llamativo que, en el transcurso de una hora no hubiera una ducha disponible. Imagino que en días donde la asistencia sea mayor esto debe ser un problema. Y, hablando de una actividad que debería sea relajante, puede estropear toda la experiencia.
Otro punto que me llamó la atención fue la oferta de té. Tanto en room service como en el bar decía "Selección de tés". Sin embargo, la elección era de lo más normal. Creo que un hotel como este debería poder ofrecer, además de lo normal, algo superior (siempre pensando en mejorar la experiencia). Podría decir lo mismo del café, pero entiendo que para esto se necesitaría un barista y puede ser que no tengan esta demanda, pero el té es más simple.
Otro punto que quería traer era la falta de batas en la habitación y en la zona de la pileta. Si bien se resuelve pidiéndolas, creo que se podría agregar al servicio de la habitación (cuando pregunté me dijeron que siempre se piden).
Como dije antes, estas cosas son pequeñas, pero creo que detalles como estos hacen la diferencia entre un hotel y otro.
Ediliciamente el hotel está muy bien, y la atención personal es correcta. Pero en esta categoría son cosas esperables.
Quiero aclarar que esta crítica está hecha con la mejor voluntad. No hay en ella ningún ánimo de ofender a nadie.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: Todos los puntos están cubiertos en mi primer texto

Name: LEONARDO
Overall Comment:
Reseña del  :

Mi reciente estancia en el   fue una experiencia gratificante en muchos aspectos, principalmente gracias al excepcional servicio proporcionado por su personal. Desde el momento en que llegamos, nos recibieron con una cálida bienvenida y nos brindaron asistencia en todas nuestras necesidades.

El personal del   demostró un compromiso excepcional con la satisfacción del cliente. Siempre estaban dispuestos a resolver cualquier situación que surgiera durante nuestra estadía. Desde preguntas sobre las comodidades del hotel hasta solicitudes especiales, el equipo estuvo disponible y dispuesto a ayudar en todo momento.

Sin embargo, hubo algunas áreas en las que notamos algunas deficiencias. Por ejemplo, el jacuzzi en los baños no funcionaba durante nuestra estancia, lo cual fue decepcionante ya que esperábamos disfrutar de esa comodidad. Además, nos vimos obligados a cambiarnos de habitación debido a la insuficiente iluminación en el baño de nuestra habitación inicial. Aunque el personal manejó la situación de manera eficiente y nos ayudó a cambiar de habitación sin problemas, este inconveniente inicial fue un contratiempo.

Además, observamos un pequeño inconveniente en cuanto a la cantidad de toallas proporcionadas en las habitaciones. En una habitación para cuatro personas, notamos que si se dejaban solo dos toallas en el baño, automáticamente generaba una llamada a recepción. Aunque apreciamos la atención al detalle, esta política podría revisarse para brindar una experiencia aún más fluida para los huéspedes.

A pesar de estos contratiempos menores, el personal del   siempre respondió de manera profesional y eficiente a nuestras preocupaciones, lo que mitigó cualquier inconveniente que pudiera haber surgido. En general, mi experiencia en el   fue positiva, gracias en gran parte al excepcional servicio brindado por su dedicado personal.

I also cannot recommend the location, although it's close to central BA, the traffic is loud and the area is plagued with homelessness and petty crime. Sorry, but there are nicer hotels in more tourist friendly areas.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: See initial review....this hotel does not provide the   experience I expect.

The window drapes were broken so they were extremely hard to close. The bathroom was all glass, unfrosted glass with no curtains or blinds, so any visitors or staff could see you in the shower if they came in your room. Overall Comment: On the whole our stay was good. There seemed to be a lack of knowledge with regards to the coffee amenities in each room.
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
We felt communication was lacking in our requests being filled.  Our room had a kettle and instant coffee packs. This is absolutely fine but more should be available at the front desk. We had to ask repeatedly for more coffee each day and trying to convey we did not have a coffee machine therefore could not use pods became frustrating as we kept getting the wrong thing. A comment regarding the portion sizes. A normal club sandwich is 3 slices of bread with the fillings. The fact that 2 full sandwiches (6 slices of bread) and fries was the serving here is extremely wasteful as we can’t imagine many people would be able to consume that amount of food. We gave the extra sandwich to a homeless person with a child.  There were a lot of staff in the restaurant doing nothing but only one bartender in Ruby Bar who found it difficult to keep up with bar and table service.  Finally - we arrived at the hotel at 7:45am and realized this is well before check-in time and fully expected to wait. We were told our room would be queued for housekeeping. As a Gold Member I am shocked that we did not get our room until 3:45pm. I believe they were readying rooms for a group arrival but as GM of a hotel in Canada I feel that the individual guests have to be prioritized as well. 
Joel on the front desk was the standout team member for our stay. Kudos to him.

Reason for Brand Question Rating: It was four of us, including my wife, my 7-year-old daughter and my 13-year-old daughter (just turned 13 in November), and we only booked one room. We were staying at Hilton Buenos Aires for four nights before checking in at   Buenos Aires. Hilton gave us a double-bed room and didn't raise any concern on the limitation of occupants. Though I totally understand each brand and individual hotel may have different policies regarding numbers of occupants, I wasn't appreciated the way I was treated. I was asked to speak to a reservation manager over the phone, who told me in a very demanding tone and unfriendly way that I had to book another room.  I don't understand why the check-in desk couldn't explain this to me face to face. I felt a bit of discrimination and humiliated. Yes, part of the reason of booking one room was to save cost, and it was also because my wife wasn't comfortable to have the two girls stayed in a separate room by themselves. I requested two connecting rooms after I booked another room on the spot, but I was told there wasn't any connecting rooms available.  We were forced to stay in two separate rooms.

Name: TODD
Overall Comment:
I had great stay at the Buenos Aires  . Staff was friendly and helpful (particularly in the lounge).  Facilities were sufficient, and the location is extremely convenient for exploration of BA.  

That said, there are some things that could be improved upon. Specifically, I'd like to see a wider selection at breakfast.  It's pretty meager compared to similarly priced and branded  s across Asia / Oceania.  It was often hard to find a table at breakfast -- tables weren't bussed very quickly.  And the front doors of the hotel need some serious maintenance.

Many others have noted that the property is a little dated; while this is true, I didn't find that it impacted my stay in away. Housekeeping was great and everything in my room was top notch and in working order.
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
Others have complained about the age of the property;  I personally didn't find that to be a problem.

But there is a glaring weakness: some of the staff just aren't very friendly.  For example, the entrance doors are *very* sticky and hard to open.  Nobody opened the door, greeted me, or helped with luggage.  I usually travel with a digital piano and this would have been a real struggle just to get into the hotel.  Once inside, I noticed a group of bellboys / concierge staff just standing well back from the front doors talking amongst themselves.

And it wasn't just when I arrived. Every time I came and went from the hotel, they'd be standing around, apparently doing nothing. They never helped, or said hello, or anything - just indifferent stares.  Very weird and not welcoming.

I contrast this with  s across Asia where the bellboys and concierge staff greet you at the door, help you with luggage, just say hello and ask if there is anything you need.

At breakfast, there may (or may not) have been a to-order omlet or egg station. Nobody told me but I saw other patrons with omelets. Some mornings it was hard to find a table because tables hadn't been cleared in a timely manner.

If there was one thing that could be done to improve the hotel, it would simply be to increase the attentiveness of the staff.  It doesn't have to be anything major, they should just be looking for things to do, ask if people need assistance, etc.  And this should be applicable to guests who are non-native Spanish speakers, too.

I was very pleased with the hotel.  Staff were helpful and competent.  The rooms were showing their age, but were clean and well maintained.  The buffet breakfast offered a good choice of healthy items in a pleasing atmosphere.  We also enjoyed an excellent meal in the main dining room.  Front desk staff were helpful on check in and departure.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: I was very satisfied with every aspect of my experience at this hotel.

Overall Comment: Very comfortable- great location BUT I do have some feedback to offer you!  Please consider increasing your price and do not charge for coffee packets/associated accoutrements. Overall Comment: Muy placentera nuestra estadía, lo único que no me gusto fue que el día sábado había una convención, y cuando fuimos a almorzar al restaurante, no solo la carta era extremadamente escasa, sino que pedimos ensaladas, y nos las trajeron en bowl de plástico, como si las hubieran comprado en McDonald (LITERAL). entendemos que haya una convención, pero uno paga por un servicio 5 estrellas, y ese día no estaban a la altura.

Name: MICHELLE
Overall Comment:
Beautiful hotel in the heart of Buenos Aires... but my room wasn't cleaned as promised when I went out so I came back to a dirty room and grabbed my dirty towels to give to the maid down the hall ("oh sorry, we were told to clean another room") and came back to my key not working. Long story short, 3 trips back and forth to the front desk for new keys they finally sent maintenance who spent 45 minutes with a hallway of   employees and then said the battery was dead on my door and they would need to come back in an hour. I needed to shower, work and rest before my evening plans (tango lessons then tango dinner) so I asked them to change my room. While they worked on my door lock, there was 5   employees in my room and in the hall, I work in the legal field so I was unable to make the confidential phone calls needed for work in California. When I first asked for a manager at the beginning of this fiasco, I was told there wasn't one available and that there physically wasn't one at the hotel (?!?!).. only when my tour manager called and complained to them did they have a manager show up. He offered me lounge access for my trouble (I've now lost 3+ hours of work time).. I told him you can keep your lounge access, I need to work in the room. He apologized and admitted that "there were two managers behind this wall and the GM is upstairs and none of them like to deal with customers" so they did not respond when requested!!!!!

Are you kidding me? Another Gate One client Nishta was standing with me, glad I had a witness to this unbelievable statement by the Manager of Public Relations for   Buenos Aires hotel.

They finally give me a new room at my request, I move everything and spend the night in a sweat thinking I must be coming down with a fever. In the morning, I realize the AC doesn't work! I call the manager, who sends someone who confirms yes, it's broken.

I pack up and move rooms again, to my third room in the  . Settle in, unpack, begin working and then attempt to flush the toilet, which doesn't flush. I called and they sent someone to fix it.

I am in shock about this hotel and what garbage it is, and for a manager to tell me that the other managers don't want to deal with me so I wasted 3 hours dealing with being locked out of my room without management assistance- unbelievable.

I should mention, each time I moved rooms I was downgraded- the OPPOSITE of what should have happened!!!
I went from a room with a small view of the street, to a view of ac units outside with the USB plugs not working, to a tiny room with an uglier view. I have told my local friends who were going to come stay at the hotel not to spend a penny to stay here.

Here are photos from the three rooms as they went downhill quickly.

first room, which I was locked out of it and they couldn't fit the lock within the 3 hours:
unnamed (2).jpg
2nd room with broken AC, third small room w a garbage view as well:
405485171_10168652320850161_8279356624287710214_n (1).jpg401344836_10168654452630161_736445211010261528_n.jpg

Please let me know what   will do to make this up to me, this is unacceptable. I have traveled with Gate 1 many times over the years and have never experienced anything like this. In fact, in the 49 yrs of my life, traveling the world, I've never had a hotel manager tell me their other managers refused to deal with me because they don't like dealing with customers.
I will be awaiting your timely response.
Thank you,
Michelle Gredinberg 408-438-1636

I have stayed in various  -branded hotels in all over the world. The BA   was one of the worst experiences I have now. Moreover, I had convinced my other 2 friends also to book the same the BA   and they too got the same worst experiances and now I am totally embarrassed and lost the credibility.
My room # was 830 and my 2 friends got 6th and 10th floors.
The front of the hotel looks so outdated, not cleaned, broken ceiling lights, and homeless nest.
The front desk staff was not interactive, appears he just wanted to finish his duty. I had to ask questions to find out about the facilities like, what are available, wifi detail, operation time, etc.
Room # 830 was one of the worst rooms I have stayed so far in hotels. The linens were cloudly white (not crisp), wood floor was dirty with gaps, wallpapers were ripped off, bathroom door was patched after flood, etc. (too much to points here).  I took a few pictures as well to share with Expedia and   CEO.
I was with my 3 family friends on a Patagonia trip for 2 weeks. The BA   had ruined my last day of stay in BA. Other less-known hotels were much better than the BA  . I would definitely going to ask   CEO for a full refund to me and my friends.

Name: JOHN
Overall Comment: The doorman/concierge was welcoming and helpful but the initial desk clerk did not provide a warm greeting, but having traveled across Argentina it seems to be a national trait to be miserable.   However, he was efficient as were the ladies on the desk when we needed help.  The hotel itself was clean but showed severe signs of wear and tear (ripped sofas that no one had attempted to repair).   The bar offered Mojitos but couldn't serve them for the entire stay because no one could be bothered to step outside and buy some limes.  The restaurant staff were poorly trained and more interested in talking to eachother than serving their guests.  The sausages you serve at breakfast were indescribably awful so I assume were genuine Argentine versions since all Argentine food (unless it's barbecued meat) is that bad - either flavourless or disgusting, or both.  The room was OK but showed signs of wear and tear and hot water was only hot in the morning and evening and we had to ask for the aircon to be enabled.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: See previous input. You need to invest in a) staff training b) better management and c) fixing things like torn sofas - it was more trailer park than trusted hotel.

Name: GONZALO
Overall Comment:
El servicio fue muy malo.
Tenía 2 noches y pretendían que una de las noches la pasara en una habitación y la otra noche en otra.
Les dije que de ninguna manera y la opción que me plantearon fue que esperara 25 minutos que limpiaban una habitación y ahí si no había necesidad de cambiarme. Nosotros llegamos a las 19:20 aproximadamente y tuvimos que esperar casi media hora para que nos den la habitación cuando el chek in arranca a las 15.
Adicionalmente nos pasó que a la 1 y media de la mañana luego de salir deun evento empresarial en el propio hotel mi esposa se fue a la habitación y no le abría la puerta la tarjeta. Fue a la recepción y le dijeron que no podían darle otra tarjeta porque no sabían quien era!!! Al estar en un evento el el propio hotel ni esposa no tenía el documento, lo había dejado en l habitación. Finalmente luego que quejarse una persona la acompañó a la habitación y el problema se solución.En resumen fue una muy mala experiencia, con algunas personas totalmente carente de sentido común.
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
Además de la mala atención y servicio detallada anteriormente, se suma que uno de los ducheros, el que tiene mampara de vidrio no se podía entrar.
Estaba rota y trancada la puerta de vidrio.
No se si estaba clausurado por gusto o estaba roto, pero en cualquiera de los dos casos me parece un desastre para una habitación de un  . No es lo que uno espera.

Name: CHRISTINA
Overall Comment:
After my debacle in Tupungato, almost anything would have been better. That said I was so wonderfully surprised by the smiles, and the level of service from both the front desk and the concierge lounge. This was truly the level of service I’ve come to expect over the years. Florencia Sananes was the bright star of each morning, and the front desk guy (I wrote down the name, but now can’t find it - Sandy blondish hair, beard always has the computer on the far right if you are facing the team) was so helpful and unnecessarily apologetic when he couldn’t upgraded me on my first stay. All and all an amazing stay.

My one piece of constructive feedback… on the night of November 8th, my friends and I were waiting in the lobby for the van to take us to La Ventana for the tango show (magnificent recommendation by Florencia). The security team member patrolling the lobby saw me sitting on the desk (not the couch) on the left side as you enter the lobby area from the street… came up to me… pointed and waved his walkie talkie at me… as if to say… “get off”. He didn’t come up and nicely ask me to move… if he had I would have explained that soft couches hurt my back and I had just walked 10 miles that day… but the pointing really bothered me. Just a little coaching…. It’s better to walk up and provide an explanation then to point like that.

Regardless, I look forward to recommending the hotel in my blog and suggesting to everyone they should stay here. 

Thank you for a great visit!

Second. The pool. I absolutely love the pool. However the basin requires some cleaning. When you are in the pool and approach the edges You can see that tiles of the basin having a heavy black plaque. Also water taps in shower cabins in the pool are not in a good shape and it’s very hard to control the water. This actually brings me to third. 
Third. There is an overall issue of maintenance in the hotel. It seems that over time the natural wear of hotel appliances, furniture, and facilities haven’t been addressed properly. I have been in various rooms during my stays and in each and every room there were many small maintenance problems, which always left a little feeling of neglect. I haven’t always complained about it, because I don’t like to make a hassle from little things. but even my colleagues who stayed with me in this hotel said the same.
Going back to the positives, the M-Club is also nice and convenient and the guys working there a super kind and helpful. 
Overall I love the hotel and the stuff and I always happy to come back

Night shift impeccable, always available and looking to do their best for their guests. 

I was celebrating my engagement during my stay in Buenos Aires, and I had a reservation at a different hotel under the   flag, but unfortunately didn’t meet the requirements for a nice and comfortable stay, so having had great experiences before hand at the   hotels around the world, and specially coming from the hospitality industry, I was very disappointed when I got a card whishing me happy birthday.

And the most important of all, by the treatment I got from one of the front desk agents, Macarena was ABSOLUTELY rude over the phone, demanding and totally disrespectful towards myself, reaching the point to raise the voice to me.

I totally understand the responsibilities and what the procedures requires, but such a behavior was totally not acceptable and totally not what the brand represents and should present to their guests. 

Agustin on the other hand was so nice and had such a touch while dealing with situations and adversities that I faced during my stay, having issues with my bank, having to wait for almost an hour to get my card enabled to transactions abroad.

Him and the night shift employees must have my thank you for the great stay and all their efforts to make my engagement celebration the most memorable possible.

I totally understand the responsibilities and what the procedures requires, but such a behavior was totally not acceptable and totally not what the brand represents and should present to their guests. 

Agustin on the other hand was so nice and had such a touch while dealing with situations and adversities that I faced during my stay, having issues with my bank, having to wait for almost an hour to get my card enabled to transactions abroad.

Him and the night shift employees must have my thank you for the great stay and all their efforts to make my engagement celebration the most memorable possible

Overall Comment:
Everything about the hotel and my stay were wonderful. From Check-in through check-out I thought the service was perfect and my room was very comfortable and clean. 
All of the employees with whom I interacted were professional, friendly and super helpful. I would especially like to acknowledge the following employees: 
Luciana (front desk/check-in) Thank you for the early check in and late check out and the other recommendations you made for me

Florenzia (M Club) - Thank you for helping start my day on the positive way with your friendly greetings and warm smile when I had breakfast in the M Club.  Also thank you for recommendations for places to visit around Buenos Aires

Nelson (M Club) Thank you for also helping start my day in a positive way  - always a friendly and warm greeting when I would go the M Club and wonderful all around service - even remembering what kind of omelet I wanted when I would order one.

Antonella (M Club) - Thank you for also starting or continuing my day in a positive warm way. Always friendly greetings and warm smile when I went to the M Club.  Also thank you for recommendations for places to visit around Buenos Aires

There was another young woman who worked in the evenings at the M Club and I apologize I don't have her name.  She was always friendly and helpful - warm smile and very kind. 

Juan Manuel (front desk a/check out)- Thank you for making a key so I could wait in the M Club after check out and while I waited for my car to the airport

To hotel management - you did a wonderful job in hiring these employees and I hope you value them.  All of them, especially those in the M Club made me feel at home - and that goes a long way for me being a stranger and first time visitor to Buenos Aires.   I look forward to may next visit and will definitely recommend the hotel.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: See my previous comment.  As a result of the excellent customer service I felt completely at home during my stay.

Portanto os hóspedes que vão tomar café 1h antes do término já não podem desfrutar de todos os itens que o hotel dispõe em seu café da manhã.  Além disso colocam os talheres direto sobre jogos americanos,  ao invés de disporem sobre guardanapos de tecido.  Um hotel 5 estrelas deveria abolir jogos americanos que não conseguem ser adequadamente limpos de um hospede para o outro e usar apenas toalhas e guardanapos limpos entre um hóspede e outro.
Outro ponto negativo para um hotel 5 estrelas foi o fato do hotel nao restringir pessoas em traje de banho durante o cafe da manhã. Em 2 manhãs havia um rapaz enrolado de toalha constrangendo a todos que estavam no café.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: Pelo relato que já que fiz anteriormente.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Buenas tardes, gracias por contactarme y querer saber mi opinión.
La realidad es que fui con muchas expectativas y mucho entusiasmo pero volví bastante decepcionada. 
Llegue 15:45 hs aprox y me dicen que la habitación no estaba disponible. Consulto si el check in era 15 hs ya que creí que me había confundido y que había llegado antes, la persona que me atiende me indica que efectivamente es a las 15 hs pero que como contaban con mucha demanda todavía no estaba lista. Acepto ya que podía suceder. Me pide DNI de las personas que nos íbamos a hospedar, en este caso yo y mi hijo de 9 años. Me indica que debe tomar copias de nuestros DNI y quedárselas. Se los lleva y demora bastante en volver. Decido alejarme de la recepción y sentarme a esperar. Cuando regresa me dice que no puede cobrarme ni tomar la habitación ya que el sistema no se lo permitía. Acepto y le digo que espero. Luego de unos minutos sin explicarme nada me pide una tarjeta de crédito como garantía (lo normal de cualquier hotel) pero no me indica el valor por el que va a hacer la pre-autorización, ni me lo muestra, ni me dice que luego lo anularían ni nada, solo pasa la tarjeta y se queda con él voucher. Le explico que no prefería pagar mi estadía con esa tarjeta sino que voy a realizar el pago en efectivo. En ese momento queda disponible la habitación y puede tomarla. No me indica el tipo de cambio, solo me dice que son $90465.-, le doy $90500.- y me dice que no cuenta con cambio para darme el vuelto. Le digo que no hay problema, asumo que es un importe menor. Me dice que no me puede dar la factura, que me la va a enviar a la habitación, le digo que no hay problema sin embargo la factura jamás me llego. 
Me voy a la habitación, la asignada fue la Nro 1230, un tanto decepcionada por la mala impresión inicial.
Al día siguiente me retiro, la chica que me atiende no me presta demasiada atención. Le pido la factura indicándole que no me la habían dado ni enviado a la habitación. Me la pone en un sobre, me la entrega y se dirige a atender a otra persona. 
El día viernes 21 me contacta el banco emisor de mi tarjeta diciéndome que tenían pendiente un cobro de $120.000.- del día 18/07, les explico que seguramente había sido un bloqueo por parte del hotel y me indican que se encuentra pendiente de cobro que por favor me contacté con el hotel y revoquen ese voucher para que no se efectúe el cobro. La persona que me atiende por teléfono me dice que efectivamente fue una preutorizacion y no un cobro que ma va a enviar por mail la anulación de ese voucher y la factura que yo había abonado en efectivo. Recibí al mail el voucher que indicaba pre autorizacion. No estaba la factura que yo había abonado pero de todos modos yo la tenía física en papel.
Esperaba mucho más del hotel en cuanto a la atención, las instalaciones muy prolijas, todo muy limpio y ordenado, confortable y agradables los ambientes. 
Agradezco la cordialidad de tomarse su tiempo para leer mi experiencia.
Saludos.

Name: FRANCISCO
Overall Comment:
Fue una experiencia maravillosa. Nos encantó la habitación y lo mejor por lejos fue el spa del piso 23 y sus hermosas vistas!

Pero para que sigan subiendo en los ratings, si, debo mencionar algunas situaciones que podrían estar mejor manejadas:

1) A la hora de cenar quisimos ir al Celtic Bar. Preguntamos en la recepción donde quedaba. Nos indicaron. Fuimos hasta allí y se encontraba vacío y con unas sogas en la entrada. Volvimos a la recepción y les contamos lo que encontramos y recién ahí averiguaron y se enteraron que estaba cerrado. No deberían saber de antemano que restaurantes o bares se encuentran abiertos y funcionado??

2) Cenamos en La Luciérnaga. Allí tuvimos 2 inconvenientes. 
El primero, luego de ingresar al restaurante nos sentamos en una mesa. A la cual nos trajeron el menú, luego nos acercaron una silla extra para que colocáramos la cartera. Una vez que vino el mozo y ordenamos la cena el propio mozo nos pidió que por favor nos cambiáramos de mesa ya que el se encontraba atendiendo en las mesas que se encontraban 3 filas más atrás!! Eso me pareció muy mal. Tener que levantarnos y cambiar de mesa luego de ordenar??? Esa situación fue la primera vez para mi- y muy incómoda.
El segundo inconveniente surgió cuando mi marido pidió el ojo de bife estilo argentino en su punto jugoso. El bife lamentablemente lo trajeron cocido la primera vez y aún más cocido la segunda vez. A raíz de todo esto, mi marido debió pedirse un plato de pasta (que según el estuvo delicioso) pero la experiencia de cena fue tremendamente mala ya que mientras yo comía mi plato principal mi marido me tuvo que mirar (sin tener el su plato para cenar) y mientras el ceno yo lo mire comer ya que yo ya había terminado con mi plato. Cenamos a destiempo.

Name: ROMINA
Overall Comment: It was very frustrating from the beginning that we requested a room that had a bathroom with ventilation (air extractor, anything) every day I would be told that they were at capacity. I’ve stay for 7 nights. You would think that at some point they would save a room with the same qualities that had air extractor in the bathroom but no. It did not happened. I felt I was getting played. The manager would call me and said that he’d find a solution that day but nothing. The bathroom with air circulating, it was like a sauna and stayed like that for over 2 hours. All the vapor would come inside the bedroom. I told them that my dad was getting sick from it. No one care, they didn’t not do anything. They wanted to give me a smaller room with tiny twin beds but with the air extractor. How hard was to keep the same room but with the air extractor. I called at least 2, 3 times a day and nothing. Ridiculous, horrible customer service. The manager I believe was Roberto or Antonio said I could probably bring you a fan to the room. How cheap is that, awful suggestion. Well, they never changed my room so my dad and I are sick now. In addition, one night I showered with cold water, the heater was not working. The first night the sheets smelled dirty, I requested a changed. 2 nights after the sheets had stains. I asked for coffee to the room, it never showed up. They forgot it. I traveled all over and I never been in a situation were in 7 days can not fix a guest request. Nor try to accommodate the guest in some way maybe even after a day. They’d tell me oh by tomorrow and just like that they played me every day. I’d leave notes for the manager and nothing. It’s sad because it’s a beautiful hotel. The bell desk guys were lovely. But my room was a sauna and now me and my dad are sick

Overall Comment:
Very friendly and professional staff.  Quick turnaround with questions or assistance I needed.  Excellent food and dining facilities.  Bar has the wide variety of treats.  Gorgeous view from the 23rd floor, decent swimming pool, good offer of treadmills equipment.

On the downside:  the room facilities require maintenance refresh/upgrade. Stucko cracks, windows not closing tight, etc. 

Gym equipment upstairs (power lifting room) has old equipment, it would be worth investing in a set of modern products like Technogym.

IT support: while staff is very friendly and eager to help, the equipment lags behind - guest WiFi hot spots work intermittently bad, I recommend to perform a wifi coverage survey and upgrade equipment accordingly.  Eventually I had to connect to the hotel IT department's wifi - which worked much more reliably.

Overall Comment: Overall, I had a very nice stay at the Buenos Aires  .  I think, though, that it's time to refresh the guest rooms, they seem a bit outdated and tired.  In my room, 1214, the shower head placement was not good.  It directly in the middle of the tub which caused water to go all over the floor of the bathroom; also, if the water was to cold or too hot it meant stepping into the stream of water to adjust the controls.  This placement should be reconfigured.  Finally, I had European-style electrical plugs which didn't fit in the sockets in the room.  It would be nice to either upgrade the electrical sockets to universal-style (which allow multiple countries' plugs) or to have Argentina to European adapters available for guests to use.  I had to go and buy my own adapter (which, on a Sunday was quite a trek to find an open store).

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Es un gran hotel 5 estrellas ubicado en pleno centro de Buenos Aires frente al obelisco. El lobby es enorme y apto para reuniones en varios espacios con sillones. La recepción es pequeña, pero rápida con agua gratis para el pasajero y sillones cercanos. El restaurante está en el mismo lobby, al alcance.
Tiene 2 torres; la principal con 21 pisos y un Spa en el 23º. La atención a los pasajeros es cordial y rápida.
Las habitaciones son amplias, cuentan con escritorio y acceso a internet gratis. El baño es pequeño en las habitaciones standard. Cuenta con agua caliente con gran presión.
Los ascensores son rápidos.
El Spa está en el techo: cuenta con piscina con agua caliente y un pequeño espacio al aire libre en una terraza con gran vista a la ciudad. Desde los ventanales del Spa se ven imágenes de la ciudad imperdibles. El gimnasio está ubicado más arriba con excelentes vistas. Cuenta con sauna y espacios para masajes.
El desayuno está incluido en el restaurant del lobby; con muy buena oferta para iniciar el día.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Buenos días. 
Llegué temprano al hotel y mi habitación estaba lista, pero me comentaron que no podía entrar hasta las 14.00/15.00. 
Teniendo en cuenta que la habitación ya estaba lista y preparada, realmente no entendía por qué no podía pasar puesto que no suponía ningún esfuerzo adicional para el hotel. Soy miembro del club. 
En cualquier caso la persona que me atendió en recepción, a pesar de la sugerencia del pago consiguió que pudiese entrar sin gastos, lo cual agradecí muchísimo. Llegaba de un viaje largo y tenía una reunión importante y necesitaba por lo menos, descansar y prepararme para dicha reunión. La entrada a la habitación fueron unas 3 horas antes aprox de lo que hubiese sido la entrada habitual del check in. 

Con esto quiero decir, que es importante este tipo de servicio a los que optamos por alojarnos en   y quizás este tipo de detalles marcan la diferencia de elegir un hotel u otro. 

Estuve muy agradecida a la persona de recepción que me atendió. 
Por otro lado, quiero hacer una mención especial a Carlos que es la persona que está en la puerta (sr de pelo blanco con ojos claros) que ayuda con las maletas. 
Un sr educado, de buen humor siempre y dispuesto a ayudar. La vez anterior que estuve en su hotel, él mismo me atendió y le recordaba nítidamente. 

La actitud de esta persona: amigable, educado y sonriente también marca la diferencia en los hoteles. Al final el trato humano es necesario e imprescindible. 

Por último comentar que no soy una persona muy especialita con las habitaciones, pero sugiero que informen al personal de limpieza que los que están alojados en habitaciones pegadas al cuarto desde donde salen los carritos, tengan más cuidado con los ruidos. Estaba en la habitación 1826 y todos los días sobre las 6.30 a.m. se oían golpes de sacar el carro. Cada día era mi despertador. :(

Muchas gracias por permitirme la posibilidad de compartir mi experiencia en  . 

Sin duda, volveré a este hotel. 
Gracias y que tengan buen día. 
Sara Navarrete Trokenheim
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
Como indicado en mi primer comentario, al principio fue un poco complicado, pero finalmente se solucionó el inconveniente. 
Es cierto que las habitaciones (por lo menos la que yo tenía) estaba bastante antigua. Quizás una reforma de las habitaciones (si son todas como la que yo estaba) estaría bastante bien. Sobre todo por el concepto que tenemos de   hoteles.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
To whom it may concern,
 
Today, after four nights at Buenos Aires  , I did the checkout from room 1528 and made a complaint about the noise coming from room 1527 from 2:45 am to approximately 4:00am. The two rooms are connected by a closed door with two inches of air openings, so you are able to perfectly heard what is happening next door. At first, I recorded the "Karaoke session," extremely loud, and called the Front desk/security (2:45am.) The person from security came upstairs, stayed for 2 minutes, and left without any warnings to room 1527. Then, about 30 minutes later, there was a big argument on the 1527 room, and it became a kind of abusive sexual behavior. Once more, I reported the issues to front desk/security and I did not want to get involved. I do not want to present charges against to the police as I am not a party to the aggression. I just request as a   member/guest to please 1. improve safety protocol, this was an uncomfortable situation, and 2. please check if the woman is fine and healthy and proceed as such. If you provide me with a phone number or share drive, I could share the videos I obtained from my room.
 
Sincerely,
 
Guillermo
Member # 099654816

No vale 300+ dólares la noche, por ese dinero buscar un hotel mejor

We returned from the walk, checked at the front desk and a room was available.  They said they'd send the bags up.  We went to the room and my wife immediately laid down for a nap.  I waited for the bags to be delivered.  After about 40 minutes, I went to the front desk and the bellman had no idea that we were waiting for bags or any idea as to where our bags were. We immediately went back to the front desk and at first we were told there were no more rooms……then a room was found in the other tower of the hotel.  As we were traveling with another couple who had a room next to us, we certainly were not pleased with this as our only option.  Due to the fact that we were delayed in getting to our room by having to go to front desk to resolve this and the fact that the room type we received was not available and we had to go to another tower, we asked for some type of accommodation for this inconvenience.  We are   Rewards members (Granted….not a high level), however we were not offered any discount on this room, or a credit towards future stays.   Disappointed in that.  Otherwise are stay was fine.

2) No nos dijo por cuanto estábamos pasando la tarjeta, que eran más de 2 millones de pesos argentinos. Nosotros no preguntamos, pero veníamos de un vuelo de 14 horas.

3) Cancelamos las noches, salvo la primera que si tuvimos que pagar, que fueron alrededor de 1150 dólares, pero cuando le llamamos en la noche todos desesperados primero nos dijo que “si se podía pero qué tal vez nos iban a cobrar una multa”, le llamamos otra vez horas más tarde y ahí si nos dijo que no habría que pagar nada.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Hello  -Team,

We have been looking forward to stay at this property but have been disappointed by the hotel on many occasions. Below you will find a list of objective items. Overall, a nice hotel, our room was very nice and most staff friendly. 

Check-in experience 
During check-in (first reservation from 24th to 26th of February), I was not specifically welcomed as a rewards member. I was also not informed during check-in that our rate includes a dinner at the hotel’s restaurant. Usually, hotels provide a welcome letter with all relevant details and benefits. However, we have been told that our room will be ready by around 12 am and that they will inform us using the   app chat functionality. My attempt to contact them by the chat functionality also did not result in a status update. Around 3:30 pm we went back to the reception to inquire the status of our room, which was ready by then. 

Items included in the rate not delivered 
Our second reservation for an upper suite from 26th to 27th of February also included a dinner and bottle of champagne (according to rate details). We did not receive a bottle of champagne. In addition, the pictures presented on the hotel website suggest that we would have flowers, some pastry and a wide choice of Nescafé in our room. This was not the case. 

Dinner arrangements 
I noticed myself on the 25th late evening when I rechecked the reservation for details on the price that a dinner was included. I asked at the Restaurant around 10 pm if it was possible to have a single dinner for three (including my wife’s sister)  on the 26th instead of two single dinners (for the first dinner it was too late anyway on the 25th). My request was rejected. The next day I asked at the reception if they could arrange for an exception. They told me to check with the manger and to get back to me. I also informed them that they never informed me about the dinner option included in the rate. They never informed us about any result and we hat to take dinner outside the hotel together with my sister in law. 

Forgotten Taxi reservation 
On the 26th we asked the front desk around 9 pm to make a reservation for a taxi to the airport next day at 10am. We have been waiting outside for a taxi that never arrived because the front desk forgot to reserve a taxi for us. I had to call a taxi myself and assist the taxi driver to put my luggage into the car. There was no attention by the hotel staff. 

In addition, we noticed the following:
Our bathroom light was flickering, they fixed it upon my request 
The pool was not meeting my expectations (I know the pool from before corona). Inside the water I saw a significant number of small particles floating. Some of the tiles were so dirty that people already wrote limpiame (clean me) on them. We only went once to the pool. I would have liked to spend more time at the pool, but given the water condition I rather avoided it. 
The breakfast is better in other hotels, at the  : poor quality, coffee comes only from a machine (where is the barista), fried eggs, Omelettes etc. have not been offered, the medialunas (Argentinian croissants) are much better in any random bakery outside the hotel. Consequently, we went only once for breakfast inside the hotel.
Reason for Brand Question Rating:

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Adoro o   Buenos Aires desde que era Hotel Panamericano, especialmente devido ao Spa e piscina no piso 23. 

No entanto, nas minhas ultimas estadas, sinto que sou praticamente um hospede incomodo, pois a clara prioridade de todo o staff está em atender os muitos grupos estrangeiros que estao preferindo o hotel neste momento. 

Em minhas ultimas 3 estadas, nos ultimos 2 meses, este é o unico hotel onde nao obtenho nenhum tipo de servico adicional por ser membro de Bonvoy. Tentei em diferentes ocasioes, possíveis upgrades ou late check-outs sem sucesso. 

Mesmo entendendo que estes benefícios sao vinculados a sua eventual disponibilidade, o que me incomoda é a falta de boa vontade por parte do staff em nem sequer tentar / averiguar a possibilidade e apenas responder que nao e que estao lotados. 

Como sempre em Argentina, me parece uma visao míope, preferindo atender de forma prioritaria ao turista ocasional, que atualmente vem a Argentina pela diferenca cambiaria, vs atender ao viajante corporativo que vai seguir visitando a Argentina em diferentes momentos do país. 

Seguirei considerando o   Buenos Aires dentro das minhas alternativas, mas no momento priorizarei o Sheraton ou outro hotel onde em geral sou melhor tratado.
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
É um bom hotel, em linha com a expectativa que se tem sobre um hotel da bandeira  . 

Nao posso dizer o mesmo sobre a expectativa que se tem de um servico especial aos sócios premium de Bonvoy, onde o staff do   Buenos Aires deixa a desejar.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Favorable comments:  staff were pleasant and accommodated a room change while laundry was processing and laundered garments were correctly sent to the new room
Considerations for improvement:  Suggest upgrading in-room electrical sockets with international plug configurations, suggest upgrading in-room electrical sockets with USB charging, suggest adding face washing cloths/rags for personal hygiene to supplies provided in guest rooms, suggest adding facial tissue to supplies provided in guest rooms, suggest replacing working tables with hairy leather hide - it is difficult to write on papers or use computer mouse devices (recommend avoiding surfaces which are difficult to use computer mouse devices like glass)
Unfavorable service:  during my stay, there were two days where my initial room 1511 was inundated with a smoke smell and I requested to change with the telephone operator who said they would check and call back.  I NEVER received any call back about it either day.  On the first day (Saturday) I approached the front desk about changing rooms and was informed the hotel was full; unfavorable but expected during tourist season on the weekend.  On the following day I called again because the smoke smell persisted and again did not receive any response.  Fortunately front desk personnel were able to organize a different room for the remainder of my stay.

Reason for Brand Question Rating:
La experiencia es muy cambiante. Hay días en los que el staff del Restaurant o el bar del Lobby puede ser atenta y otros en los que toma más de 20 minutos recibir atención, se olvidan las ordenes, etc.

La calidad al recibir el servicio es excelente, pero si es extraño que haya tanta disparidad en el servicio o en los productos ofrecidos.

Un ejemplo de esto sería que estuvo un carrito de bebidas para ser restockeadas un par de horas afuera del M Club y no había bebidas de cierto tipo en el Club. El club estaba con staff suficiente para hacer el restocking, etc. pero no se percataban de que estaba el carrito afuera o tenían otras prioridades en ese momento. 

También hay casos en los que no retiran los cubiertos/comida de mesas que ya están sin clientes en el Club, esto a veces se extiende a horas en los que no se retiran restos de comida, etc.

Habiendo dejado eso en claro vuelvo a reiterar que el staff de recepción, el personal de limpieza y del área de Spa/Gimnasio es absolutamente perfecto.

When we agreed to sit there they told us it was 1500 arp per person, I repeated 1500 arp and they said yes. When I went to pay the bill it was 9500 arp per person.  I would not have paid that much for mediocre food. 
Lastly we left a bag with my sons soccer jersey and a plaque behind at the buffet lunch. The next day I called the hotel and asked if they had found something and they couldn’t help me and told me to send an email to which I have not received a response. 
Having gone to multiple  ’s in my lifetime this is not the experience I expected and will make me question if I should ever stay in one again.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
My room was not up to the standard   is known for.  Shower leaked into the bathroom floor, toilet flush valve didn’t always catch causing the water to run, no bathroom counter to lay out personal toiletries, bathroom exhaust fan had a loud bearing, no full length mirror, limited closet space for a week stay, I heard what I believe were mice at night running in the wall.  The next two experiences were really the worst. 1) Every door to the rooms on the 15th floor with the automatic closer SLAMMED shut every night. The door in the adjacent room slammed so hard it shook the bed and bedside table causing my phone to fall on the floor.  It sound like a bomb going off and was very disorienting.  At 3am, is not a restful sleep. Each of the door closers need to be adjusted or replaced with silencers. 2) the smoke detector above the bed flashed constantly illuminating the room at night.  At some point each night the signal would make the light burn brightly solid and right into my eye. Not very restful. 

As you exit the elevator on the 15th floor, you have a trip hazard where the finished floor doesn’t match the elevator opening as was sloped to meet. Morning coffee machines didn’t always work and are too close to several patron tables. Poor circulation at the coffee station. 

The good things. All the staff were super friendly. Fresh breakfast offered with a nice selection. Great baggage storage system. The car service was great. Beautiful pool (even though a little small). Loved all the comfortable available seating in the lobby. Clean public bathrooms on the main floor.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment:
Several weeks ago, I booked three rooms for the Buenos Aires   for myself and two friends. I used four suite nights to upgrade my room since I would be staying at the hotel for several days and was hoping for a spacious room with a decent view. Within two days of my trip, I received a confirmation that my upgrade request had been accepted for a deluxe city view suite with a sitting area.

We were scheduled to arrive at the hotel after midnight on Friday, November 4 so I contacted the hotel to make them aware of this on Thursday and again on Friday. They confirmed that they made a note of my reservation and that our three rooms would be available when we arrived. 

When we arrived at check-in we were presented paperwork to sign for our rooms and get our keys. I reminded them that I was Platinum elite and my room had been upgraded. They told me room 1626 was the upgraded room. When I went to my room, it was not only small and cramped, it was next to the service area and the elevators. The detached shower head did not work properly and there was water all over the floor after a less than 5 minute shower. The television in my room did not work, I played with the cords but could not get it a signal. The safe also did not work. I requested three times for someone to come fix it.

Later that day, I went to see my two friends’ rooms and both were nearly twice the square footage and had lovely city views. Immediately, I went downstairs with my Spanish-speaking friend to see where the mix up occurred. At the front desk, they told me that nothing else was available. We even asked if they was a standard room, which would have been larger than mine, and they claimed they would try to see what they could do. 

After speaking with several front desk staff during our stay, they never accommodated me as a Platinum, soon to be Titanium, elite member. Instead, I spent four night in a cramped room with a broken television, poor views and had to endure listening to the repeated chiming of the elevators, as well as hearing the housekeeping carts and other staff come in and out of the area next to my room.

As a 1.) platinum elite member, soon to be titanium, 2.) owner of a   timeshare and 3.)   cardholder of 10+ years who has spent tens of thousands of dollars this year, I expect to receive better treatment and service. The poor experience and mediocre customer service definitely left a sour taste in my mouth.

This message is going to the hotel and   corporate. I have also sent a message on Twitter.

I should have just gotten one myself because they are normally 4-5000 pesos so make sure you double check what the price is before you have them call a taxi for you. I didnt think about it until i was halfway there and my friend that lives there told me that was too expensive and so did the uber app which tells approximately what they will cost for taxis. It would have been cheaper if i walked outside and waved one down myself.  So lesson learned and double check the prices before you get in a taxi especially if they tell you a flat rate

Varios inconvenientes:
Desde un principio se hizo especial aclaración que el pago lo realizaría la Cía. y como no garantizaban la reserva se dejó una Tarjeta de Crédito personal . No obstante, al ingreso del pasajero, le solicitan la TC o el pago de la reserva, un papelón… lo termina pagando un particular. Dos días despues reclaman el pago a la Cia.,  se realiza, informan q se duplicó el pago y que el saldo quedará a favor… Al reclamar la devolución me la realizarán a tres días de recibido el pago duplicado…
Amén de todos estos inconvenientes los pasajeros informaron que el servicio no fue bueno (hablamos de una habitación Deluxe c/vistas):
-Ingresaron el sábado pero el servicio de habitación (limpieza-cambio de toallas-etc) se realizó el día lunes a pedido del huésped.
-Solicitaron una ensalada aclarando q la querían sin pollo -por ser vegetariana- y vino llena de pollo.
-Papas fritas “saladas” 
-Habitación de ese costo con el sanitario con falta de revoque en pared.
Lo único a favor que recalcaron fue la atención del personal del spa y piscina y el desayuno pero la verdad es que sobran motivos para no volver a tomar una reserva con vuestro hotel.

Overall Comment:
La verdad fue una decepción. Llegamos para el check in a las 15 hrs como estaba previsto y recién nos dieron la habitación a las 18:30 y luego de insistir. 
Hicimos tiempo en el área de la psicina y nos dieron mal una llave del locker y el chico que la fue a cambiar demoraba, entonces sale mi novio a ver que pasaba y estaba charlando con otra empleada en las escaleras, y la respuesta fue "me entretuve charlando, perdón".
El servicio del bar no es acorde a un hotel de está categoría. Los vasos de plástico para servirse los diversos jugos que ofrecen, restan muchísima categoría. La carta de tragos es muy limitada y los mismos también se sirven en vasos de plástico duro. No tengo problema en pagar un trago carisimo como pagué este, pero lo mínimo que uno espera es que esté bien presentado, con vajilla, tamaño y acorde a lo que uno está pagando.
Casi todo el personal que nos atendio, muy floja la atención, con la excepción de la Sra Fernanda Ayala que nos atendió sumamente bien durante el desayuno. 
Desde ya que no nos compensaron con un late check out, luego de las más de 3 horas de demora que tuvimos para ingresar a la habitación. 
Fue una invitación sorpresa que le hice a mi novio por su cumpleaños y la verdad, no resultó buena. No volvería.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment: The rooms need an upgrade. I stayed on the left side facing an alley with a bunch of engines that ran nonstop. You could hear them throughout the night. Either stop using those rooms facing the alley or change the windows to soundproof.  The wifi went off at the rooms and no one notified us. I had to go work from a coffee shop! Finally, I left an item in the room after checking out and when I reached out to inquire about it I was told they did not find anything. I made my way into the airport to catch my flight and not even 20 minutes later the hotel reached out to tell me they did find the item. I asked them to please ship it to my US address as I was already at the airport, explained that had they checked properly when I asked the first time I could’ve stopped by the hotel on my way to the airport. The hotel response was that they could not bring it to me to the airport (which I did not ask for) or ship it, but that they could keep it for me so I could pick it next time I came to Buenos Aires. Are you kidding me? Very disappointed to say the least, regretted using my   points for this.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: Please read previous comments regarding poor wifi, facilities in need of upgrade, sound proof windows for rooms facing alley with a bunch of running engines, and terrible customer service when staff refused to ship an item I left behind

Name: MARIA
Reason for Brand Question Rating:
Staff at the club lounge were all very attentive and engaging. Also even prior to arrival, my ambassador status was recognised with an upgrade available upon check-in. This made my birthday stay wonderful.

I do have to say though that on the day of my birthday, I was expecting like a small cake or complementary greeting which I had during my birthday at Westin Gurgaon in India a few years ago. I understand this is not standard and would be something that is above and beyond.

It was strange though that upon arriving to the room after check in, there was an envelope/ letter that seemed to be a welcome note for A DIFFERENT Guest. I never received a welcome letter while it was strange to find one with someone else’s name. This made me think I was in the wrong room so I had to call front desk. Was just a confusing arrival in that sense.

Other than that. Everything was ok.

Regarding the spa experience. One evening, the fire alarm rang while in the sauna on the top floor. My partner got dressed immediately and ran out and was advised that it was safe to continue as the alarm was in the womens changing room/ sauna that had caught “fire” and the water extinguishers turned on. That was a strange / unusual experience.

     The one issue I had was with the maintenance of the rooms. The cleanliness was excellent, but the room looked as though it had been flooded multiple times. Wallpaper was peeling, missing grout, rotting baseboards, and water stains were all over the bathroom. The chairs in the main room were peeling, Iron had burnt crap on it that stained my shirt. I have made four business trips to Buenos Aires in four different hotels, most of which were at the significantly cheaper end of the spectrum than a  . This was clearly at the bottom in terms of room condition and quality.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: I have only been a member of Bonvoy for about a year and most of my time has been spent in Houston at what appeared to be a very new hotel. It was perfect. Pretty inconsistent, but it is only a comparison of two hotels.

La piscina y las instalaciones comunes son el punto alto debido a la preciosa vista desde el obelisco y las completas instalaciones. El punto bajo es que en la habitación existe una puerta que colinda con otra habitación, el cual no tiene aislación de sonido, escuchando a nuestro vecino conversar hasta las 2 de la mañana por telefono, lo que no corresponde con la calidad del hotel y el precio pagado para una estancia tranquila, además se debería incluir una carta en la habitación para indicar los valores de los consumibles en el frigobar, ya que en otros hoteles de 5 estrellas (fuera de la argentina, este fue nuestro primer hotel en buenos aires) las bebidas, café y demasés que se incorporan dentro de la habitación son cortesía del hotel. En nuestra opinión, recomendariamos el pago de los programas por un día, pero no las habitaciones classics.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: Entre los servicios utilizados, la piscina maravillosa, el sauna es bueno, el desayuno muy completo, pero la incomodidad de no tener un buen aislamiento y escuchar a los vecinos conversando toda la noche, no fueron una buena experiencia con respecto a la comidad de la habitación.

Name: MARIA
Overall Comment: This hotel is perfectly located on Avenida 9 de Julio, steps away from one of the main city attractions the Obelisco and easy access to other key streets like Avenida Corrientes, Cordoba, Carlos Pellegrini. Its just opposite the Porteño Tango theatre and the Teatro Colon.  Very nearby, walking distance you can get to the other main attractions like the Plaza de Mayo, Casa Rosada, el Cabildo and the Cathedral. The rooms are well appointed and maintained. Ours featured a sitting area at the entrance, a generous closet with a safe, large toilet & bath/shower area and comfortable king bed, with our window looking right out onto the avenue and the Obelisco.  In general staff were helpful and courteous, got us reservations popular restaurants and gave great tips for things to do and places to see.

Social Comment:
Luego de leer los comentarios del hotel tenía una serie de dudas importantes, por ejemplo los obreros trabajando, la piscina cerrada, el cierre de Tomo 1, etc.
Al ser socio Gold me dieron un upgrade al piso 17 al frente con balcón, excelente habitación, renovada, estuvimos hospedados cinco noches, el servicio impecable.
Tomo 1 cerrado, obreros trabajando nunca los vimos y no sentimos ruidos, la piscina abierta con gimnasio y vistas panorámicas increíbles.
Utilizamos el estacionamiento con servicio de parking muy bueno, algún problema que tuvimos lo solucionaron inmediatamente, mucho personal, mi señora perdió una caravana importante en la habitación  y lograron encontrarla, fantástico !!!
El edificio desde afuera parece envejecido, no se nota salvo en el cartel la llegada de   , la ubicación es perfecta, mucha limpieza, buen trato, buen servicio que nos tiene acostumbrados. Lo del título muy buena experiencia, prontos para repetirla !!!

Name: ANIBAL
Overall Comment:
Tuvimos una experiencia muy positiva en el hotel; destacamos la calidad de la habitación y la muy buena atención y propuestas recibidas en el desayuno y restaurante, así como la excelente disposición del personal de asistencia con el equipaje. Celebramos las mejoras en el gimnasio, aunque consideramos que aún deben hacerse inversiones en puesta a punto del equipamiento. La única debilidad a mencionar es la prologada demora en el servicio de habitación, tanto para proveernos de elementos de uso (toallas, secador de pelo), como para los pedidos de comida.
Sin dudas volveremos al hotel a la brevedad.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: Se percibe un esfuerzo continuo en mejorar las instalaciones y el servicio, y el esmero del personal en brindar una atención adecuada. Es entendible que una infraestructura tan grande requiera grandes inversiones de mantenimiento y mejora, que seguramente se continuarán en forma gradual.

En segundo lugar, yo había agregado una noche pero lamentablemente no me podía quedar en la misma habitación porque ya estaba reservada y me llegan a la habitación 1023 y no fue lindo la verdad: la bañera no tenía vidrio, por tanto, toda el agua se salía para afuera; la cortina tenía sangre, la sabana había pelos, la verdad que se notaba que la estaban arreglando y me mandaron a mi ahí. La verdad que estuvo muy lindo hasta que me enviaron a la habitación 1023 y hasta que el empleado se metió en mi habitación sin mi consentimiento.

Name: Nos_qui_sumus
Social Comment:
We stayed over a week a this property. It is centrally located right next to the Obelisk. Although it is not Recoletta / Palermo, where most of the bars and restaurants are located we didn’t have any problems getting around thanks to Cabify.

Although it is an old hotel, the rooms have been thoroughly refurbished and are of a decent size. Breakfast could have a few more options and an additional coffee making machine would help, but this was a minor inconvenience. There is a very decent gym and a swimming pool on the top floor. 

The truly differentiating factor was the quality of the service. It was efficient and to the point. The front desk’s dinning recommendations were top notch and they were super helpful securing recommendations. Kuddos to Luciana!

Reason for Brand Question Rating: Man kommt sich als Gast nicht willkommen vor. Es wird nur versucht Geld zu machen (Taxis, bar bezahlte Getränke werden auf die Rechnung gesetzt). Vor allem von dem jungen Hausdiener, der am 30.07. Vormittag Dienst hatte wurde man auf Spanisch beleidigt, weil man monierte, dass der Preis für das Taxi innerhalb von 5' um 20% stieg.

Name: MEHMET
Overall Comment:
Five-star location, comfort, breakfast, reception Four-star pool, Two-star amenities and room size
8.0

Liked  · The location of    is perfect. Walking distance (10-15 minutes) to fancy Recoleta, to Plaza Mayo and Puerto Madero close by, Tango show across the street (Avenida 9 de Julio), to Buquebus ferry (to Colonia de Sacramento),100 meters to Calle Corrientes and 50 meters to the "Cambio, Cambio" places. "Cambio, cambio", i.e., the blue dollar market, is the current reality of Buenos Aires (BA). The street value of USD is almost double the value of the official price. Therefore exchanging USD on the street doubles (more or less) the life standard of the Tourists. This was the first time I didn't pay the hotel with my credit card. Rather I exchanged the USD with Blue Dollar rate and paid the hotel with cash. Of course I was anxious. "I don't know the currency, how can I be sure that I am not given fake money", "Largest bill is 1000 Pezos which is more or less 3.5 USD so even for one night I have to give 30-40 bills so for a week long stay a huge pile of money I have to give to the reception", etc. made me anxious. So I decided to pay in installments. Reception was very welcoming. I exchanged 100 USD in a Cambio place, paid it to the Hotel. This ensured me that the pezos I receive were not fake. Two-three days later I paid another installment to the hotel with the bills I received from the same Cambio place. Ana two-three days later I paid the final installment. That's it! Yes when you pay with cash there is +%21 more, however the exchange rate is double so it is still better option for me. The rooftop pool was also very nice. Weekends and late evening on weekdays it was relatively crowded, however other times it was very quiet and enough to enjoy swimming. There is also Sauna as well as gym that one can use. The bed and the pillows were perfect for us. I enjoy hard pillows, my wife enjoys soft and we had both in the room. :)

Disliked  · We chose the cheapest and the smallest room in the facility. It was really very small. The bathroom was large, however the bedroom was very small. Only bed and a small table fitted to the available space. I guess I would have chosen a larger room if I returned back to BA. On the other hand, there were no toothbrush, shaving kits provided in the bathroom. Nor daily drinking water (only two bottles of water when we arrived). I believe the situation in Argentina is kind of dire due to the economical instability and this influenced the service provided by the hotel to the guests. I would expect more from a five-star hotel in that sense. Hairdryer was not available in the bathroom so we had to ask for one. In five minutes they brought it, however, as I have said, in a five star hotel I wouldn't expect such a thing...LAST BUT NOT LEAST: The pictures provided in the website is misleading for Classic Room!
Reason for Brand Question Rating:

La cena en la luciernaga tambien un lujo! Quisimos hacernos masajes pero creemos que estaba un poco caro el precio por eso no nos lo hicimos. 
Y para terminar, el dia domingo 17 habia una convención y se lleno de policías y detectores y nos pareció muy incomodo que nos revisaran de arriba abajo cada vez que entrabamos si salíamos siendo huéspedes. Hubiese estado bueno que controlen a los que iban a la convención unicamente.
Reason for Brand Question Rating: Desde el minuto cero que nos hicieron sentir como huespedes vip. Fue una gran experiencia!

Não se conseguia tomar banho sem encharcar o banheiro todo. Box minúsculo. Tinha que se ligar a água com a porta do box aberta o que molhava todo piso. Tomadas de 3 pinos (sistema argentino). Sem adaptador disponível. E outras pequenas mazelas que derrubaram o conceito do hotel. Inúmeras vezes nos hospedamos na rede Merriot e nunca nos deparamos com algo tão sofrível como desta vez. Lembro que dois meses antes - no mesmo hotel - a hospedagem foi muito boa.

Social Comment: Ok I decided to stay a weekend at this hotel.  Normally stay at another    affiliate.  This hotel was refurbished and they did an awesome job.  I was upgraded to a suite. Good AC, TV Channels, Comfortable bed (pillows a little hard though), M Club was open all day and most of the evening/night, centrally located (close to Avenida Florida)...on main street so a little noisy but rooms were solid enough to prevent most of the noise.  I was so impressed that I left the other hotel (changed during weekdays) after one day and came back.  Was given another suite in the other tower (there are two) and the room was more modern and updated than the previous.  I definitely would stay again.  One note...this hotel caters to Gate 1 and other tourist / sports groups so it can get crowded and noisy in the lobby.  Hotel is priced appropriately.  Better than other    brands/affiliates. La pileta es hermosa. El personal muy atento. El restaurante y los espacios comunes del hotel están muy bonitos. En principio nos tocó la torre nueva y linda del hotel. El detalle era que en una de las dos habitaciones no funcionaba el agua caliente y los cuatro debíamos bañarnos en la otra habitación. Recién en la cuarta noche de estadía nos cambiaron de habitaciones, sin bonificación alguna por los inconvenientes. Nos tuvieron dos horas esperando con nuestros hijos, con las valijas hechas, para llevarnos a una torre que no ha sido remodelada, nos otorgaron habitaciones viejas y por mucho que lo nieguen, la torre norte es de menor categoría. Pisos rayados, empapelados sucios, sin extractor en baños. Espantoso. Eso si, por primera vez y tuvimos agua caliente en las dos habitaciones que abonamos.

se la pasan pidiendo disculpas por los inconvenientes, pero en cuatro días de estadía no brindaron una solución satisfactoria. Quisiera que el gerente del hotel se comunicara personalmente, y me responda por estas cuestiones, ya que la gente de la administra no ha sido eficiente en soluciones.
